                                    <watches>7</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="65438" author="jhammond" created="Fri, 30 Aug 2013 14:20:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Folded into HSM timestamps and ownership issue &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3811&quot; title=&quot;non-root users cannot archive files, root cannot archive non-root users&amp;#39; files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65151" author="jhammond" created="Tue, 27 Aug 2013 13:04:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please see &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7461&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7461&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64968" author="jhammond" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2013 16:46:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are we planning to support a non-root copytool? This is news to me. At very least it needs CAP_FOWNER, CAP_DAC_OVERRIDE and maybe some others.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By original process, do you mean the copytool?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64962" author="adilger" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2013 16:30:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The volatile file should be created by the MDS with the ownership of the original process as with any newly-created file, otherwise the non-root copytool will not have permission to chown() the file (nor should it be able to).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
